    {
      "name": "register_agent_via_cpi",
      "docs": [
        "PDA-signed CPI chain into `agent_registry_8004::register_with_options`",
        "followed by `atom_engine::initialize_stats`. One TrustGate instruction",
        "lands a fully atom-functional Quantu agent (agent_account + atom_stats),",
        "hiding Quantu's two-instruction onboarding pair from MCP / SDK callers.",
        "Idempotency is enforced upstream by Quantu's own `init` constraints on",
        "`agent_account` and `atom_stats`; a second call for the same",
        "`asset_seed` fails at the first CPI boundary."
      ],
      "discriminator": [
        39,
        134,
        166,
        245,
        218,
        200,
        44,
        40
      ],
      "accounts": [
        {
          "name": "payer",
          "writable": true,
          "signer": true
        },
        {
          "name": "asset",
          "docs": [
            "The new agent's asset Keypair must sign — Quantu's",
            "`register_with_options` requires `asset` as a signer because it mints",
            "the corresponding MPL Core asset under the same key."
          ],
          "writable": true,
          "signer": true
        },
        {
          "name": "authority",
          "docs": [
            "TrustGate authority PDA — used as the `invoke_signed` seed-signer for",
            "parity with `emit_feedback` / `dispute_payment`. Quantu's",
            "`register_with_options` and `initialize_stats` do not include this",
            "PDA in their account lists, so the seeds sign for an account Quantu",
            "does not require. Kept here so the MCP threads exactly the same",
            "authority through every TrustGate CPI and so future Quantu",
            "instructions can hook the same PDA.",
            "",
            "`init_if_needed`: a fresh facilitator wallet has no",
            "`TrustGateAuthority` yet, so the prepended MCP self-heal must be",
            "able to create it inline. On first call this allocates + zeroes the",
            "account; the handler then populates the same fields as",
            "`init_authority`. On subsequent calls Anchor reads the existing",
            "account and the handler re-validates the facilitator binding (the",
            "`constraint = authority.facilitator == payer.key()` we dropped here)."
          ],
          "writable": true,
          "pda": {
            "seeds": [
              {
                "kind": "const",
                "value": [
                  116,
                  114,
                  117,
                  115,
                  116,
                  103,
                  97,
                  116,
                  101,
                  95,
                  97,
                  117,
                  116,
                  104
                ]
              },
              {
                "kind": "account",
                "path": "payer"
              }
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "system_program",
          "address": "11111111111111111111111111111111"
        }
